Stakeholder Analysis:
Stakeholder analysis involves identifying individuals or groups who have an interest in or are affected by the CookSnap â€“
Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images. These stakeholders are categorized as primary and secondary based on their level of direct involvement
with the system.

Primary Stakeholders:
Primary stakeholders are those who directly interact with and are most affected by the system.

End Users (Home Cooks, Students, and Working Professionals)
Users interact with CookSnap to upload grocery images, view detected ingredients, and receive recipe recommendations. Their main interest is saving time, reducing food wastage, and receiving accurate and easy-to-follow cooking suggestions.

System Developers / Project Team
Developers are responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining the CookSnap system. Their interest lies in ensuring system accuracy, usability, performance, and successful project delivery.

Project Instructor / Evaluator
The instructor evaluates the system based on requirement completeness, design quality, and correct application of software engineering principles.

Secondary Stakeholders:
Secondary stakeholders do not interact with the system on a daily basis but are indirectly affected by its implementation and outcomes.

Recipe Data Providers / Content Sources
These stakeholders provide recipe datasets used by the system. Their interest is proper usage and representation of recipe content.

Platform Administrators / Hosting Providers
They are responsible for hosting, system availability, scalability, and basic infrastructure support.

Future Maintainers or Researchers
Individuals who may extend or enhance the system in the future benefit from clear documentation and modular system design.
